"""
PART II Entitlement and amount

4A. Meaning of “qualifying young person”

Editorial note: current text valid from 2025-03-21.

(4)

“Approved training” means training in pursuance of arrangements made under section 2(1) of the Employment and Training Act 1973 or section 2(3) of the Enterprise and New Towns (Scotland) Act 1990 which is approved by the Secretary of State for the purposes of regulation 5 of the Universal Credit Regulations 2013.
"""

approved_training_4A_4:
    entity: Person
    period: Month
    dtype: Boolean
    from 2025-03-21:
        if secretary_of_state_approves_training_for_universal_credit_regulation_5
           and training_in_pursuance_of_employment_and_training_act_1973_section_2_1_arrangements_or_enterprise_and_new_towns_scotland_act_1990_section_2_3_arrangements:
            true
        else:
            false

secretary_of_state_approves_training_for_universal_credit_regulation_5:
    entity: Person
    period: Month
    dtype: Boolean

training_in_pursuance_of_employment_and_training_act_1973_section_2_1_arrangements_or_enterprise_and_new_towns_scotland_act_1990_section_2_3_arrangements:
    entity: Person
    period: Month
    dtype: Boolean
